Deprecated API

Contents

  • Deprecated Interfaces
  • Deprecated Classes
  • Deprecated Methods
  • Deprecated Constructors
  • Deprecated Interfaces 
    Interface and Description
    com.github.restdriver.serverdriver.http.BodyableRequestModifier
    There is now no distinction between different requests. Bodies are allowed anywhere! You should extend AnyRequestModifier instead.
  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    com.github.restdriver.clientdriver.example.ClientDriverUnitTest
    As of version 1.0.7 replaced by ClientDriverRule
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    com.github.restdriver.serverdriver.Xml.asXml(String)
    Instead of doing asXml(response.getContent()) you can now do asXml(response).
    com.github.restdriver.serverdriver.http.RequestBody.getContent()
    This shouldn't need to be exposed. Expect it to go away in the future.
    com.github.restdriver.serverdriver.http.RequestBody.getContentType()
    This shouldn't need to be exposed. Expect it to go away in the future.
    com.github.restdriver.clientdriver.RestClientDriver.giveResponse(String)
    Use RestClientDriver.giveResponse(String, String) instead.
    com.github.restdriver.clientdriver.ClientDriverResponse.withContentType(String)
    You shouldn't need to use this method any more. Use one of the creator methods which specifies a content-type.
  • Deprecated Constructors 
    Constructor and Description
    com.github.restdriver.clientdriver.ClientDriverResponse(String)
    Use ClientDriverResponse.ClientDriverResponse(String, String) instead.
